With Peterson's function, the moments of the photon energy spectrum are numerically calculated. We have a0 = 1 from normalization. a1 is simply zero because we define the b-quark mass is the average value of the distribution function f (x) times the meson mass mB. In fact, our definition of b-quark mass aims at this feature of QCD. The second moment is derived as

